Dear colleagues,

We're thrilled to share news of our upcoming online course titled "Meta-Analysis in R" happening from May 13 to 16. 

Course details and registration can be found at: [ https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/metain-r/ ]( https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/metain-r/ ) 

This course offers a comprehensive introduction to contemporary meta-analysis techniques. Topics covered include the systematic review process, statistical analysis, result interpretation, and presentation. We'll explore parameter estimation, statistical nuances, random-effects meta-analysis, meta-regression, model diagnostics, sensitivity analyses, and more. Practical tutorials will utilize authentic meta-analytic datasets, ensuring hands-on engagement to grasp various methodologies.

