Dear all,
we're excited to announce our upcoming online course on "Mapping and Spatial Operations in R: Using R as a GIS," scheduled for May 6-10, 2024. 
 
Course website: https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/gis-in-r2/
 
 
Did you know that you can perform GIS operations using R? This course offers both theoretical insights and practical hands-on sessions on utilizing R as a GIS tool. Participants will learn how to automate and reproduce mapping and spatial analysis of environmental data using R scripts.
 

This course is designed for researchers and practitioners interested in mapping and spatial analysis of biodiversity and environmental data. Familiarity with computers is required, and prior basic experience with R is strongly recommended. All R scripts will be provided and thoroughly explained to facilitate learning.
 
By the end of the course, participants will:
- Understand the fundamentals of GIS, mapping, and cartographic projections
- Acquire spatial data and import them into R for map creation
- Perform various spatial analyses using R
- Generate and export maps depicting analysis results
 
 
